WEBVTT

1
00:00:08.875 --> 00:00:11.125
[birds chirping]

2
00:00:14.708 --> 00:00:15.875
[man] Come!

3
00:00:27.291 --> 00:00:29.000
- [girl screaming]
- [gasps]

4
00:00:40.250 --> 00:00:44.166
["Dey My Side" by Worlasi playing]

5
00:01:05.166 --> 00:01:07.476
[in Sotho] I was going to get
Phila to help you downstairs.

6
00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:09.250
[in English] I can manage.

7
00:01:09.333 --> 00:01:10.666
[in Sotho] How are you feeling?

8
00:01:28.500 --> 00:01:30.833
[Zinhle in Englsih]
Morning. Mam' Grace. Bab' Don.

9
00:01:31.333 --> 00:01:33.750
Is it too much to expect
a cup of coffee here?

10
00:01:33.833 --> 00:01:36.791
Rooibos... tea.

11
00:01:49.666 --> 00:01:53.041
Here you go. Ngcolosi.
You're looking well.

12
00:01:53.125 --> 00:01:56.000
[men laughing]

13
00:01:58.125 --> 00:01:59.125
[clears throat]

14
00:02:00.708 --> 00:02:02.148
[in Xhosa] How are you feeling. Dad?

15
00:02:02.208 --> 00:02:05.375
[in English] You do not need
to talk to me like I'm dying.

16
00:02:06.250 --> 00:02:07.291
All right?

17
00:02:07.375 --> 00:02:09.375
[Phila] That is very good to hear.

18
00:02:09.916 --> 00:02:10.791
Good morning.

19
00:02:10.875 --> 00:02:13.434
[Don in Xhosa] Where is your sister?
I want to talk to all of you.

20
00:02:13.458 --> 00:02:14.791
Talk to them about what?

21
00:02:14.875 --> 00:02:15.875
[in English] Business.

22
00:02:19.791 --> 00:02:21.083
[Linda in Xhosa] Morning. Dad.

23
00:02:22.458 --> 00:02:23.625
[in English] How you feeling?

24
00:02:24.208 --> 00:02:25.250
[Don in Xhosa] Sit down.

25
00:02:25.833 --> 00:02:28.125
- [in English] Okay.
- [Don] I have something to say.

26
00:02:28.208 --> 00:02:30.541
[in Sotho]
Take your breakfast to the cottage.

27
00:02:30.625 --> 00:02:32.041
[in English] Family meeting.

28
00:02:32.125 --> 00:02:34.458
[in Xhosa] Really. Ma? Is that necessary?

29
00:02:38.125 --> 00:02:41.875
[Don in English] I'm going to slow down
significantly at the office for my health.

30
00:02:42.375 --> 00:02:43.708
[Ndu] That's great.

31
00:02:43.791 --> 00:02:45.750
It allows you to take stock of your life.

32
00:02:45.833 --> 00:02:49.125
[in Xhosa] I am going to announce
my successor at the foundation gala.

33
00:02:49.208 --> 00:02:52.625
- [in English] That's the end of the week.
- I support whatever decision you make.

34
00:02:53.666 --> 00:02:54.916
- [Don] Linda.
- Yeah?

35
00:02:55.708 --> 00:02:56.708
[in Xhosa] And you Phila.

36
00:02:57.250 --> 00:02:59.583
[in English] I'm coming
to your offices later today.

37
00:02:59.666 --> 00:03:04.333
Be ready to show me why
I should choose you as my successor.

38
00:03:10.250 --> 00:03:14.458
[in Sotho] I think I know how
we can use this succession in our favor.

39
00:03:14.541 --> 00:03:15.750
[Bonga on phone] <i>Oh. how?</i>

40
00:03:15.833 --> 00:03:20.958
If Don announces Linda as CEO.
we can reveal what we know about her.

41
00:03:21.041 --> 00:03:23.458
[in English] Make it
a big humiliation for him.

42
00:03:23.541 --> 00:03:25.625
[in Sotho] What if he picks Phila?

43
00:03:25.708 --> 00:03:27.625
[in English] We need
to make sure he doesn't.

44
00:03:27.708 --> 00:03:29.666
[in Sotho] And I think I know how.

45
00:03:29.750 --> 00:03:32.000
[Phila in English]
I don't know why you're freaking out.

46
00:03:32.083 --> 00:03:33.708
He's definitely going to choose me.

47
00:03:33.791 --> 00:03:36.250
[Grace] He was supposed
to discuss it with me first.

48
00:03:36.333 --> 00:03:37.375
You know what. Ma.

49
00:03:38.250 --> 00:03:42.041
I have been preparing
to be CEO my entire life.

50
00:03:42.125 --> 00:03:44.375
There's no way he's going
to choose Linda over me.

51
00:03:44.458 --> 00:03:45.708
Linda strokes his ego.

52
00:03:45.791 --> 00:03:48.041
[in Sotho] You need
to do exactly the same thing.

53
00:03:48.125 --> 00:03:49.916
[in English] I did not create
Bhengu Beauty

54
00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:52.708
so that another
woman's child can inherit it.

55
00:03:52.791 --> 00:03:54.625
Wow. Ma! That's harsh.

56
00:03:55.250 --> 00:03:57.708
Ndumiso. I need
your artistic eye at the studio today.

57
00:03:57.791 --> 00:04:00.791
Um. Mom. but you know I'd rather
not get involved in the company...

58
00:04:00.875 --> 00:04:03.583
[in Sotho] I need someone
to supervise Zinhle's shoot.

59
00:04:03.666 --> 00:04:05.666
I would appreciate if it were you.

60
00:04:05.750 --> 00:04:07.041
[in English] Zinhle's shoot...

61
00:04:09.291 --> 00:04:11.208
Okay. fine. I'll do it.

62
00:04:11.291 --> 00:04:13.541
I thought as much. Ahem. Bye. guys.

63
00:04:13.625 --> 00:04:16.541
Bhengu boys. remember what I said.

64
00:04:17.333 --> 00:04:18.625
Be there for your father.

65
00:04:18.708 --> 00:04:20.333
It's critical at this time.

66
00:04:20.416 --> 00:04:21.416
- Okay.
- Will do.

67
00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:24.300
- [in Sotho] You heard what I said. right?
- [both in English] Yes. Ma.

68
00:04:32.041 --> 00:04:33.041
Ngcolosi...

69
00:04:33.916 --> 00:04:34.916
Yo.

70
00:04:48.833 --> 00:04:49.833
Thank you.

71
00:05:01.500 --> 00:05:03.860
[in Sotho] Remember when Phila
used to wear his little suits

72
00:05:03.916 --> 00:05:05.333
and go to the office with you?

73
00:05:06.083 --> 00:05:08.123
[in English] He's always
followed in your footsteps.

74
00:05:08.166 --> 00:05:10.833
I have to consider them both. equally so.

75
00:05:10.916 --> 00:05:12.583
[Grace] Phila's very imaginative.

76
00:05:12.666 --> 00:05:14.875
he understands the future of beauty.

77
00:05:14.958 --> 00:05:17.166
[in Sotho] And he's the firstborn son.

78
00:05:17.250 --> 00:05:19.583
[in English]
If I chose Linda. then I'll coach her.

79
00:05:19.666 --> 00:05:22.416
- Phila's prepared to take over now.
- Grace. this is my decision.

80
00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:23.625
Alone.

81
00:05:38.791 --> 00:05:41.125
So. the new future Mrs. Bhengu...

82
00:05:41.708 --> 00:05:43.625
[in Sotho]
When will Thando and I meet her?

83
00:05:43.708 --> 00:05:46.041
[in English]
There will be no new Mrs. Bhengu...

84
00:05:49.375 --> 00:05:50.375
for now.

85
00:05:55.375 --> 00:05:57.541
[grunts]

86
00:06:00.166 --> 00:06:01.166
Grace.

87
00:06:01.791 --> 00:06:03.125
[in Xhosa] I'm not an idiot.

88
00:06:13.125 --> 00:06:14.375
[Thando in Zulu] Ngcolosi...

89
00:06:16.416 --> 00:06:17.625
can we talk?

90
00:06:18.666 --> 00:06:21.750
- [in English] It's been a few months...
- I've already told you.

91
00:06:22.375 --> 00:06:24.083
No woman leaves Don Bhengu.

92
00:06:24.750 --> 00:06:26.916
If the divorce happens
right before the wedding...

93
00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.500
That is no longer happening.

94
00:06:30.708 --> 00:06:32.666
You remain the new Mrs. Bhengu.

95
00:06:33.916 --> 00:06:35.125
Act like it.

96
00:06:46.083 --> 00:06:49.291
[Zinhle in Sotho] Make sure it gets
delivered before Don's meeting with Phila.

97
00:06:49.833 --> 00:06:51.125
[in English] Hey. Zinhle.

98
00:06:51.208 --> 00:06:52.208
Hey.

99
00:06:52.625 --> 00:06:54.083
[automated voice] <i>Going down.</i>

100
00:06:54.583 --> 00:06:56.166
What are you doing here?

101
00:06:56.791 --> 00:07:00.500
- I've never seen you at the office before.
- I'm supervising your shoot.

102
00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:02.208
[in Xhosa] Ma's busy.

103
00:07:03.333 --> 00:07:04.333
Ah.

104
00:07:04.958 --> 00:07:06.708
[automated voice] <i>Doors opening.</i>

105
00:07:08.250 --> 00:07:10.375
- [automated voice] <i>Floor eight.</i>
- [Ndu] After you.

106
00:07:18.291 --> 00:07:21.666
I'm... I'm going to say hi
and chat to Sis' Sana.

107
00:07:22.291 --> 00:07:24.166
Okay. cool. I'll check in the studio.

108
00:07:26.500 --> 00:07:28.291
[in Zulu] Hello. Sis' Sana.

109
00:07:28.375 --> 00:07:29.666
Hi. Sisi. how are you?

110
00:07:29.750 --> 00:07:31.166
I'm fine.

111
00:07:31.250 --> 00:07:35.208
I thought the vetkoek lady was only
supposed to come around at lunch?

112
00:07:35.291 --> 00:07:36.125
Is she outside?

113
00:07:36.208 --> 00:07:38.875
[in English] If I wasn't going
to the studio. I'd go down for you.

114
00:07:38.958 --> 00:07:41.916
[in Zulu] I can't believe
we're talking about vetkoeks.

115
00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:45.208
Uh... Let me see if I can catch her.

116
00:07:58.166 --> 00:08:00.916
[in English] If we look at the profits
since I started working

117
00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:03.416
with the low-income areas.
it's very evident...

118
00:08:04.875 --> 00:08:06.208
That's too corporate.

119
00:08:07.583 --> 00:08:08.625
Okay.

120
00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:16.083
Dad.

121
00:08:16.583 --> 00:08:18.625
have I ever let you down?

122
00:08:19.125 --> 00:08:21.583
[clears throat]
Yes. a few times. actually.

123
00:08:21.666 --> 00:08:22.708
[Linda scoffs]

124
00:08:22.791 --> 00:08:26.333
[as Don] Entertaining influencers
does not constitute running a business.

125
00:08:26.416 --> 00:08:27.958
- [Phila] Oh...
- [in Xhosa] My boy.

126
00:08:28.041 --> 00:08:29.875
TouchÃ©. [chuckles]

127
00:08:32.250 --> 00:08:34.750
[in English] Linda.
you know. of course. that

128
00:08:34.833 --> 00:08:39.083
you don't have to suck up to him. right?
I mean. he... he needs us.

129
00:08:39.166 --> 00:08:41.875
And so you just have to be real with him...

130
00:08:41.958 --> 00:08:44.416
You know what. Phila.
how about you do it your way

131
00:08:44.500 --> 00:08:45.500
and I do it mine?

132
00:08:47.708 --> 00:08:48.708
We're not a team.

133
00:08:48.791 --> 00:08:50.833
Okay. yes. sure but...

134
00:08:51.708 --> 00:08:54.208
I mean. come on.
you know it's no contest. right?

135
00:08:55.666 --> 00:08:59.708
[in Zulu] It's time. Linda.
Mr. Bhengu is ready for you.

136
00:09:01.125 --> 00:09:03.458
- [in English] Thank you.
- You're actually right.

137
00:09:03.541 --> 00:09:05.041
It's no contest at all.

138
00:09:09.875 --> 00:09:13.000
Oh. that's the sales report
of the partnership I started.

139
00:09:13.083 --> 00:09:14.291
Yes. I know.

140
00:09:15.583 --> 00:09:17.500
I'm not interested in numbers.

141
00:09:18.500 --> 00:09:20.583
Tell me why you are better than Phila.

142
00:09:21.875 --> 00:09:23.083
Honestly?

143
00:09:23.166 --> 00:09:24.291
Honestly.

144
00:09:28.083 --> 00:09:31.083
The fact that I didn't meet you
until I was a teenager. Tata.

145
00:09:31.166 --> 00:09:32.333
has shaped me.

146
00:09:33.291 --> 00:09:35.041
[in Xhosa] I know poverty.

147
00:09:35.125 --> 00:09:39.375
[in English] I know how it feels to be
desperate. to make it. and be somebody.

148
00:09:40.458 --> 00:09:42.958
All Phila knows is comfort.

149
00:09:43.041 --> 00:09:46.041
and comfort. Tata.
is detrimental to business.

150
00:09:48.375 --> 00:09:51.500
[" Never Let Me Go" by Tresor playing]

151
00:09:51.625 --> 00:09:52.625
[man] Nice!

152
00:09:53.458 --> 00:09:54.916
Look at the camera. Zinhle.

153
00:09:55.708 --> 00:09:59.250
Thank you. There we go.
Just lift your chin up just a little.

154
00:10:01.750 --> 00:10:04.166
Okay. look into camera for me. Zinhle.

155
00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:08.166
Look to your left.

156
00:10:10.250 --> 00:10:11.250
Into camera.

157
00:10:12.166 --> 00:10:13.541
Chin up just a bit.

158
00:10:13.625 --> 00:10:14.458
Zinhle?

159
00:10:14.541 --> 00:10:17.041
Um. may I please have a bathroom break?

160
00:10:17.125 --> 00:10:19.916
[man] Okay. cool. that's fine.
Everybody let's take 15.

161
00:10:23.583 --> 00:10:24.708
Well done.

162
00:10:24.791 --> 00:10:25.791
Thank you.

163
00:10:26.458 --> 00:10:28.000
Thanks. I'll take that.

164
00:10:29.625 --> 00:10:31.625
[suspenseful music playing]

165
00:10:44.458 --> 00:10:47.958
[Phila] If you're looking for
an eligible bachelor. that's me!

166
00:10:48.041 --> 00:10:49.708
[people laughing]

167
00:10:52.833 --> 00:10:54.250
[in Zulu] What are you doing here?

168
00:10:54.750 --> 00:10:56.500
I wanted to talk to Phila.

169
00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:00.101
[in English] Or one of his influencers.
but it seems he's still busy with them.

170
00:11:00.125 --> 00:11:03.125
- [in Zulu] What about the shoot?
- [in English] Fifteen-minute break.

171
00:11:03.208 --> 00:11:04.208
Oh. okay.

172
00:11:04.291 --> 00:11:05.541
[in Zulu] I'll see you later.

173
00:11:16.791 --> 00:11:18.511
[Phila in English]
Ready when you are. Baba.

174
00:11:18.583 --> 00:11:19.583
Let's go.

175
00:11:22.833 --> 00:11:24.875
- Oh! Hey. Yeah?
- Hi.

176
00:11:24.958 --> 00:11:27.166
I saw you talking
to some influencers earlier.

177
00:11:27.250 --> 00:11:29.583
- Yes.
- Who's the one that does makeup tutorials?

178
00:11:29.666 --> 00:11:31.375
They all do tutorials.

179
00:11:31.458 --> 00:11:32.833
No. the one that uses items...

180
00:11:32.916 --> 00:11:35.291
Listen. Zinhle. I have
to go to a meeting right now.

181
00:11:35.375 --> 00:11:37.250
You can ask somebody else. right?

182
00:11:37.333 --> 00:11:38.166
- Yes.
- Of course.

183
00:11:38.250 --> 00:11:39.250
[Phila] Thank you.

184
00:11:39.875 --> 00:11:41.041
[clears throat]

185
00:11:44.166 --> 00:11:47.166
So. when exactly am I taking over?

186
00:11:47.250 --> 00:11:49.833
Or would you like me to
make some kind of speech. or...

187
00:11:49.916 --> 00:11:52.958
You know what. I can show you
what my vision is for the company.

188
00:11:53.041 --> 00:11:55.666
- Tell you exactly how I think...
- What the hell is this?

189
00:11:56.666 --> 00:11:57.666
[Phila] That's not...

190
00:11:57.708 --> 00:11:59.958
- You're doing drugs at work now?
- It's not mine.

191
00:12:00.041 --> 00:12:03.125
- How many times have I told you?
- I don't do this at the office.

192
00:12:03.208 --> 00:12:04.791
So you admit that you still do it.

193
00:12:06.833 --> 00:12:07.833
[hesitates]

194
00:12:08.166 --> 00:12:09.333
[sucks teeth]

195
00:12:10.250 --> 00:12:12.291
Okay. Baba. but just...

196
00:12:12.375 --> 00:12:14.416
Baba. I swear this is not mine.

197
00:12:15.083 --> 00:12:16.333
It's not mine!

198
00:12:16.833 --> 00:12:19.250
I don't fucking take drugs at work!

199
00:12:28.750 --> 00:12:31.875
Um. I didn't mean to take so long.

200
00:12:32.541 --> 00:12:34.166
Where did everyone go?

201
00:12:35.625 --> 00:12:37.416
I want to try something new with you.

202
00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:40.500
You looked a little distracted.

203
00:12:40.583 --> 00:12:41.875
I wasn't distracted.

204
00:12:42.708 --> 00:12:44.625
Are you allowed to take over like this?

205
00:12:44.708 --> 00:12:46.541
I don't know. We'll find out.

206
00:12:47.333 --> 00:12:49.125
Okay. let me go and fix my makeup.

207
00:12:49.208 --> 00:12:50.708
[Ndu] There's no need for that.

208
00:12:51.958 --> 00:12:52.958
You look great.

209
00:12:55.541 --> 00:12:56.541
Okay.

210
00:13:01.125 --> 00:13:03.166
["Wish You Were Here"
by Black Coffee playing]

211
00:13:03.250 --> 00:13:04.625
[Ndu] All right. let's go.

212
00:13:05.125 --> 00:13:06.541
[chuckles]

213
00:13:09.041 --> 00:13:10.375
I love this song.

214
00:13:11.041 --> 00:13:12.041
I know you do.

215
00:13:19.041 --> 00:13:24.958
<i>â™ª The tags on the city walls
The color. the fight â™ª</i>

216
00:13:26.791 --> 00:13:29.458
<i>â™ª Ambition so tall â™ª</i>

217
00:13:30.541 --> 00:13:32.875
I don't need to resort
to dirty tricks. Phila.

218
00:13:32.958 --> 00:13:34.833
Then howÂ did that shit end up on my desk?

219
00:13:34.916 --> 00:13:36.636
I don't know.
You're the one who does drugs.

220
00:13:36.708 --> 00:13:37.916
But I don't do it at work.

221
00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:40.875
Apparently. you do.
Stop blaming me for your carelessness.

222
00:13:40.958 --> 00:13:43.250
Okay. you're so perfect. aren't you?

223
00:13:43.333 --> 00:13:44.333
Yup.

224
00:13:44.375 --> 00:13:47.375
How would you like it if
I used your secrets against you?

225
00:13:49.958 --> 00:13:51.875
- Phila. you wouldn't.
- Oh. I could.

226
00:13:52.500 --> 00:13:54.250
The difference between you and me

227
00:13:54.333 --> 00:13:56.208
is that I'm not so desperate.

228
00:14:10.458 --> 00:14:11.818
[in Sotho] What were you thinking?

229
00:14:11.875 --> 00:14:13.750
[in English]
I don't know what to tell you. Ma.

230
00:14:13.833 --> 00:14:17.333
Linda must have planted it.
You know I don't do that shit at work.

231
00:14:17.416 --> 00:14:19.541
[in Sotho] You were
high as a kite at the launch.

232
00:14:20.791 --> 00:14:22.625
[in English] That was different. okay.

233
00:14:22.708 --> 00:14:24.541
Know what. what does it matter anyway?

234
00:14:24.625 --> 00:14:26.500
I do good work. right? Don't I?

235
00:14:26.583 --> 00:14:29.083
I bring profitable partnerships
to this business.

236
00:14:29.166 --> 00:14:31.041
- Stop being so...
- So what?

237
00:14:31.125 --> 00:14:32.166
[in Sotho] Yourself.

238
00:14:32.833 --> 00:14:34.750
What's that mean?
I should stop being myself?

239
00:14:34.833 --> 00:14:37.166
If it gets you what you want. then yes.

240
00:14:38.458 --> 00:14:41.750
[emotional piano music playing]

241
00:14:55.500 --> 00:14:58.458
[in Sotho]
Now we wait for Linda's Emerald party.

242
00:14:58.541 --> 00:15:00.208
[in English] We record them as evidence.

243
00:15:00.291 --> 00:15:02.625
[Bonga in Sotho] <i>So. did you get
the entrance password?</i>

244
00:15:02.708 --> 00:15:05.375
Yes. I got it right after
you found out about her secret.

245
00:15:05.458 --> 00:15:06.541
<i>Cool.</i>

246
00:15:06.625 --> 00:15:07.541
<i>How was your day?</i>

247
00:15:07.625 --> 00:15:09.083
It was fine.

248
00:15:09.166 --> 00:15:11.333
[in English] The shoot
was relaxed for a change.

249
00:15:11.416 --> 00:15:13.333
[in Sotho]Â <i>I thought they were stressful.</i>

250
00:15:14.375 --> 00:15:15.958
Yes. but not today.

251
00:15:16.750 --> 00:15:19.583
It was with Ndu. he played some music.

252
00:15:19.666 --> 00:15:20.833
He's nice.

253
00:15:20.916 --> 00:15:22.750
<i>Nice? Are you guys friends now?</i>

254
00:15:23.666 --> 00:15:25.875
[in English]Â No. he's just...

255
00:15:29.166 --> 00:15:30.666
[in Sotho] Let's forget about that.

256
00:15:31.166 --> 00:15:34.833
You and I did great work today.

257
00:15:34.916 --> 00:15:36.125
[in English] I love you.

258
00:15:36.208 --> 00:15:40.250
[in Sotho] Please don't eat all
your meals at that barbecue place.

259
00:15:40.708 --> 00:15:42.541
[in English] Cook something healthy.

260
00:15:42.625 --> 00:15:44.041
[in Sotho]Â <i>I love you too.</i>

261
00:15:45.291 --> 00:15:47.000
["Wish You Were Here" resumes]

262
00:15:47.083 --> 00:15:53.041
<i>â™ª Wish you were here
Wish you were here â™ª</i>

263
00:15:54.375 --> 00:15:56.833
<i>â™ª Reminds me of you â™ª</i>

264
00:15:58.541 --> 00:16:02.208
<i>â™ª You hold your cards
So close to your chest â™ª</i>

265
00:16:02.291 --> 00:16:05.875
<i>â™ª That I give up the question no more â™ª</i>

266
00:16:17.333 --> 00:16:19.133
- [Grace in English] Thank you. Regina.
- Yes.

267
00:16:22.208 --> 00:16:24.208
[Grace sighs] Hey.

268
00:16:25.166 --> 00:16:26.291
[in Sotho] About Phila...

269
00:16:26.375 --> 00:16:28.208
[in English] There's nothing more to say.

270
00:16:28.291 --> 00:16:31.708
[in Sotho] I'll make sure
he never touches drugs ever again.

271
00:16:32.583 --> 00:16:34.458
We've invested so much in him.

272
00:16:34.541 --> 00:16:36.517
[in English] All that education.
the connections...

273
00:16:36.541 --> 00:16:40.875
All those expensive schools.
and all he learned was how to use drugs.

274
00:16:41.333 --> 00:16:44.750
[in Sotho] I'll drug-test him daily
if needed. I'll take him to rehab.

275
00:16:44.833 --> 00:16:48.833
His peers are millionaires.
children of ministers. CEOs.

276
00:16:48.916 --> 00:16:51.708
[in English] We can't let all
those good connections go to waste.

277
00:16:52.541 --> 00:16:55.291
[in Sotho] Pick him.
for the good of the company.

278
00:16:58.666 --> 00:17:01.000
[in English]
Is he ready to get his hands dirty?

279
00:17:01.083 --> 00:17:02.416
[in Sotho] What do you mean?

280
00:17:02.500 --> 00:17:06.416
[in English] Whoever gets to take over
will have to run both our businesses.

281
00:17:08.541 --> 00:17:10.291
Ngcolosi. is that necessary?

282
00:17:11.083 --> 00:17:13.625
Kolobe doesn't need to be managed.
I can go over things...

283
00:17:13.708 --> 00:17:14.750
No.

284
00:17:14.833 --> 00:17:18.666
Linda and Phila will have to know
about the other side of our business.

285
00:17:18.750 --> 00:17:20.875
And only then will I make my decision.

286
00:17:22.125 --> 00:17:23.166
In fact...

287
00:17:23.958 --> 00:17:26.208
[in Xhosa] ...call Peter
and tell him to bring them home.

288
00:17:28.416 --> 00:17:29.291
[in English] Now?

289
00:17:29.375 --> 00:17:31.250
Yes. now.

290
00:17:35.375 --> 00:17:37.083
[sniffing]

291
00:17:40.250 --> 00:17:42.833
[Phila] I will be with you
in 20 minutes. Peter. yes.

292
00:17:42.916 --> 00:17:45.541
- [Peter on phone]Â <i>Okay. Ciao.</i>
- Thank you very much.

293
00:17:46.458 --> 00:17:47.583
[sighs]

294
00:17:47.666 --> 00:17:52.041
[cell phone rings]

295
00:17:52.125 --> 00:17:53.000
[beeps off]

296
00:17:53.083 --> 00:17:54.791
[Phila] Well. thank you too. Mom.

297
00:18:01.041 --> 00:18:04.291
Oh. Phila. answer the damn phone.

298
00:18:05.083 --> 00:18:06.583
[in Sotho] I spoke to your father.

299
00:18:07.083 --> 00:18:09.458
There's something he wants
to share with you and Linda.

300
00:18:09.541 --> 00:18:12.291
[in English] Something very important.
Then he'll make his choice.

301
00:18:13.000 --> 00:18:15.208
Say yes to whatever he says.

302
00:18:16.375 --> 00:18:17.666
And don't freak out.

303
00:18:23.083 --> 00:18:24.291
[Thando] Sounds tense.

304
00:18:28.208 --> 00:18:30.250
Why is Ngcolosi no longer getting married?

305
00:18:31.166 --> 00:18:32.708
Ask him yourself.

306
00:18:35.125 --> 00:18:37.875
[in Zulu] Remember that...
if you had anything to do with it...

307
00:18:37.958 --> 00:18:40.250
...he'll always do whatever he wants.

308
00:18:40.333 --> 00:18:42.125
[in English]
There'll always be more chicks.

309
00:18:42.208 --> 00:18:44.625
If you do your job. there won't be.

310
00:18:46.208 --> 00:18:49.000
If you fail to control him.
how the hell do you think I can?

311
00:18:49.083 --> 00:18:50.083
Hmm?

312
00:18:51.125 --> 00:18:53.708
You're fighting
a losing battle. Mrs. Bhengu.

313
00:18:55.458 --> 00:18:57.125
Don doesn't care about us.

314
00:19:11.333 --> 00:19:12.333
Phila.

315
00:19:13.083 --> 00:19:14.541
did you listen to my message?

316
00:19:15.375 --> 00:19:16.291
[Linda] Hi. Dad.

317
00:19:16.375 --> 00:19:17.500
